Dialogs.Dialog: By the way, the store assistant who was just transferred to our restaurant didn't look happy lately.
Nene
Eh？ You mean the one with long sideburns？
Yeah, the one with those weird sideburns. I wonder what happened to him.
I heard that he was dumped by his girlfriend.
Is that so？
And I heard it was a cruel break up and he took it pretty badly. He still can't gain his footing.
That's why he's been absent-minded during work.
I see...
So, next time you have to work with him, you must watch out for him too.
I see... Okay, I'll keep that in mind.
Nene
By the way, did you see that assistant with sideburns？
I did and I was surprised.
He used to have long sideburns, but now he shaved them off...
At first, I couldn't recognize him. I thought he was a new employee.
I don't think he had changed that much...
But why did he decide to do that？
I accidentally heard it while he was chatting with others. He was heartbroken so he wanted to give himself a fresh start.
Eh？
He felt like he was reborn as a new person after he shaved his sideburns. ...That sounded like a reckless decision to me.
The manager tried to cheer him up by saying that when his sideburn grew again, the wound in his heart would slowly be cured.
So, he'll grow his sideburns again, huh...？
Nene
By the way, I haven't seen "Mr. Napoli" at our restaurant lately.
Mr. Napoli？
Ah, you don't know him？ There's a regular customer who always orders Napolitan every time, right？
Ah, that guy. Yeah, I haven't seen him lately...
Is that so？ Maybe he goes to a different restaurant now.
He might get bored of eating Napolitan, right？
No, that can't be the reason. His passion for Napolitan is real.
He's been eating our Napolitan for over a year now. He can't just get bored of it suddenly, right？
Over a year...？ I think that has passed the point where he could get bored of it, huh...？
You think so, too？ Yeah, I wonder what happened to him...
Nene
Ah, yeah. Did you know？ Earlier, Mr. Napoli has returned to Dixie's.
Ah, the customer who always orders Napolitan, right？
Yeah. And guess what he ordered this time.
Not Napolitan？
Well... He ordered carbonara.
Hey, could it be that you got the wrong person？
No, everyone remembered him. It couldn't be the wrong person.
Eh...？ Then his favorite dish has changed. I think it's just common that people change their mind, huh？
...To hear you say that, I'm feeling very insecure now... Are you going to get bored of me？
B-But we were talking about food...
Nene
By the way, have you remembered the new menus？
Menus...？ At Dixie's？
Geez... You must remember them, okay？ Did you forget what I taught you？
Now that you mention it...
At least you must remember what dishes were taken off. It'd cause problems if you took those orders from the customers.
But, when we key those items into the machine, we'll know that they are no longer available...
No. If you wait until then, you'd have to go back to take the orders again, right？
You mean the customers will have to wait longer？
It's very good that you remembered. If the service is slow, it'll affect customer satisfaction, okay？
Yeah... That'd be bad. I'll have to try to remember the new menus...
Nene
The menus at Dixie's have been changed for quite a while. Have you remembered them？
Yeah. I have.
Hehe. That's good. As your former supervisor, I feel like you've grown up.
But the list of things to remember keeps piling up. ...We're only working part-time. Does Dixie's expect too much from us？
Hmm？ Really？ I don't think so...
I wonder if it's the same if I work at a different place.
I don't know. But if they pay you to work, at least you have to work hard for them, right？
If this is how I feel when I work part-time, I wonder how it'll be for my real job...
Hehe. I don't mind working to earn more money for our family. You don't have to worry much about your salary.
That would be nice...
Eh？ ...For our family？
Nene
Ah, right. The manager mentioned that he'd have you take care of the new employee.
So, I'll have to give the new employee guidance！？
Hehe, I'm a bit worried about that.
I'm even more worried...
Really？
Well... ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲, do you think I can guide anyone...？
You'll be fine. When I had to guide you, I was also nervous at first.
▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ was nervous, too？
Yeah. So... Right！ Should I guide you how to guide others？
If you please.
Nene
It seems like everything is going well with you and the new employee.
That's thanks to ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲, I think.
Really？ I didn't do anything much for you...
When I teach the new guy, I'm trying to recall how you taught me...
Hehe... Which means you're teaching him attentively, right？
Y-Yeah？
Do you remember when I taught you how to wash the tableware...
The new employee is a guy. It's not good for me to teach him closely like that...
...If he were a girl, you'd do that？
I wouldn't. No, I mean I couldn't. I already have ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲...
Yeah, very well.
Ah, yeah. Earlier, there was a foreign customer at our restaurant. Do you remember him？
Nene
Hmm... When was it？ There are many foreign customers at our restaurant...
Really？
Yeah. They aren't very conspicuous. But there are customers who take their family to our restaurant many times a month.
Eh？ Dixie's is like an international restaurant then.
Hehe. Anyway, why did you bring this up？
Right. At that time, I was hesitating if I should greet him in English instead of Japanese.
Well, not all foreigners speak English...
That's true... Hmm, but that customer could speak Japanese fluently...
You even paid that much attention to the customer？ Hehe. I think I should be happy about this.
Nene
Ah, right. I think it might be okay to greet customers with "Hello" at our restaurant.
Why？
We say "Irasshaimase" to customers, right？ How can we translate it to English then？
Ah... We talked about foreign customers earlier. So you've been thinking about it.
But I think it's more common to greet them with "May I help you？"
Yeah. But at a restaurant, maybe we should greet them less formally. Like, "Good afternoon."
Hmm？
But I think I like to greet customers with "Irasshaimase" best.
Really？
If we use English, it's like we're thinking that they don't understand Japanese. Many foreigners can speak Japanese well.
I see.
And if we speak to them in English, it'd cause troubles to other employees who can't speak English, right？
That's right...
Nene
...Hehe.
What？
Nothing. I'm just thinking about work. There was that time when the parents brought their kids...
What happened then？
Those kids were following you and imitating your moves.
They must think that I was funny... Hah...
Hehe. Don't feel down. At least the kids liked you, okay？
Really？
I think it's a wonderful thing that kids like you.
If you say so... Hmm... I think it's not bad then.
...Haha.
Nene
What？ Why do you laugh all of a sudden...？
Sorry. I'm thinking about what happened at work. There was that kid who didn't want to leave ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲.
Ah... That boy. He was so cute.
Yeah, his mother went to the restroom to change her baby's diaper.
And then that boy somehow grabbed ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲'s skirt and wouldn't let go of it.
Hehe. Boys always like to behave like a spoiled kid in front of their mothers.
But... Does ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ look like his mother？
Geez... I think he thought of me as his older sister, not his mother.
Haha, sorry.
Nene
Ah, have you heard about Dixie's new branch？
No, this is the first time I hear that. Where will it be？
Well, it's gonna be right next to the one we're working at.
That means... It's going to be our rival？
Come on. Our branch sells well and us employees have freedom to choose our work shifts, right？
But if there's a new branch, they'll be hiring new people, too...
Yeah, I'm worried about that, too. But the headquarters seem to want to expand the business... Our manager is in trouble.
Yeah... Our manager has really been working hard...
If it's going to impact us, I wish they would cancel this new branch...
Yeah, me too...
Nene
We were talking about the new branch, whether they'd build it or not, right？
Don't tell me...
They officially canceled the plan.
Yeah！ Now, our manager can feel relieved.
Rather, it's us who should feel relieved.
Why？
Eh？ If they built a new branch, we might have to work at different places. You didn't think about that？
Right...
Geez, I've been worried all this time...
Sorry... I've never thought about not being together with ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ at all.
Ah... Geez. You're cute...
Nene
By the way... Lately, there are those junior high school girls who often come to Dixie's, right？
I think they just stop by after their prep school.
...Urgh.
What？
They come because of you. Didn't you realize that？
...No way...
It can't be helped. You're so cool and so cute. You get clumsy at times, but you're usually reliable at a crucial moment.
Umm...
I feel very uneasy about this... I trust you, but I don't feel good about it... okay？
It'll be okay. I have only ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲.
...Yeah, I know. But I still feel uneasy about it. So you should keep that in mind, okay？
Nene
By the way... Someone confessed to you, right？
Confessed？
Come on... There were those junior high school girls who often came to our restaurant.
Ah, those girls... But they didn't come anymore, right？
Yeah... But why？
I told them that I'm dating ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲. That's probably why...
...You told them.
Because they asked me if I was already dating someone... Does this cause you trouble？
No, it's just... Well... Did you tell them that I'm your girlfriend？
Of course I did.
...Okay. Then I can forgive you.
Hehe. If you're like this, no matter what you did, I can always forgive you. Hehe.
By the way, the manager said that the uniforms at Dixie's might be changed...
Nene
Yeah, I heard that, too. ...But I'm not sure about the change.
Huh？
So you haven't seen the designs for the new uniforms？
I only heard about it from the manager... Eh？ They even have the designs ready？
It's okay for male uniforms. Nothing has changed much.
...Which means there's a big change for female uniforms？
Hmm... If I only have to wear it in front of you, I might think about it...
Do you mean...
Hehe. If you insist that I should wear it, I might try to approve the new designs.
Nene
Ah, right. Did you know that the designs for Dixie's new uniforms were rejected？
Yeah. I also voted "No" for those designs.
Hehe... So you've already seen the designs, huh？
If you have to wear a uniform that short, our restaurant won't be called family restaurant anymore.
Actually, I have a sample of those uniforms. I'm thinking about trying it on and showing it to you at my house.
Just kidding. Hehe. If you're serious about it like that, I should really get a sample, huh？
As your boyfriend, I don't want anyone else to see you wearing it...
Geez... I told you I was just kidding, okay？
S-Sorry... Hahaha...
Nene
Have you got used to working at Dixie's yet？
Yeah. I always keep ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲'s words in mind that I shouldn't be so nervous.
Hehe. As expected from our restaurant's most promising employee.
Most promising employee...
The manager said that, you know？ He even said that if you need a job after you graduate, he'd hire you full-time.
That was flattery. I'm still not that good...
No, I can see that you're very reliable at work. Come on. Have confidence in yourself.
...Should I？
Hehe. Modesty is one of your good points.
It's all thanks to ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ for training me well...
By the way... Earlier, you mentioned that the manager gave me high evaluation for my work, right？
Nene
Yeah, did he say something to you？
The manager also praised ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ for being very reliable.
For him to say that... Did you force him to say it somehow？
I didn't. He trusted you, ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲, that you can handle everything. He mentioned that you've been very helpful to him.
I see... But I'm more concerned about what he thinks about you more than what he thinks about me... somehow.
Huh？
Nothing. I think our manager is honey-tongued.
Yeah, but I'm really happy to hear him praise ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲.
Because you're like my mentor.
...Geez.
Nene
Ah, that's Kuro-chan... isn't it？ I think it is.
Eh？ ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲, do you have a cat？
No. It's the stray cat that's usually around the back entrance of Dixie's. Haven't you seen it？
I think I've seen it sometimes when I took the trash out.
There usually aren't any people at the back entrance and there are some sunny spots for the cats.
Ah, that's why there are always some cats around that area.
Kuro-chan is the stray cats' boss. It's so small but other cats are afraid of it.
Huh...？ Maybe it's very strong when it fights.
I've never seen it fights though... Hehe. I'd better ask Kuro-chan next time.
Nene
Right. Do you remember Kuro-chan？
The stray cats' boss at Dixie's？ I also saw him earlier.
It's actually someone's pet cat.
But it's the stray cats' boss.
Surprising, right？ I accidentally saw it with an old lady who lives at the house near Dixie's.
It was acting very cute, like a little kitten, in front of her.
Huh...？ Even the boss also behaves itself in front of its owner.
I want to do that too.
Sometimes, I want someone to act cute like that to me too...
Umm... Well, if I'm good enough for you...
...Hehe. I'll think about it.
Nene
Hey, the frog purses are quite popular lately, right？
Eh？ You mean purses that look like a frog...？
Yeah. They are very small so people often lose them. They can only hold coins.
I think I've seen them... But, I don't know if they're popular or not. I've never heard of them though.
So, they are not popular among people in your grade, huh？
Not among the guys, but I don't know about the girls. I don't have any girls I'm close to.
...You don't？
I only talk to them if we work in the same group during classes... That's all.
Hmm...？ That's quite unexpected.
Really？ Since I already have ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲, I think that's natural.
I see... Okay, I got it.
Nene
Many girls envy me for having a younger boyfriend, but...
Why do you mention this all of a sudden？
...To tell you the truth, I'm quite worried. When some girls got close to you...
No, no. Nothing will ever happen. Even at work... Ah, do you remember the frog purse？
The one that the customer forgot？
Yeah. And did you know that its owner is a housewife？
Ah, right... Speaking of which, you're quite popular among old women, huh？
They get close to me because they just enjoy teasing me, I think.
...Yeah. I know that.
But I already have ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲, so it doesn't matter who gets close to me, right？
...Hehe. If you say that, I have no choice but to trust you. You're so crafty. Geez.
